<BaseLayout title="About — Srinivas Vedantam" activePage="about">
  <div class="page-enter">
    <div class="section">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-num">04</span>
        <h2 class="section-title">About</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="about-content">
        <p><strong>18+ years in product.</strong> Director-level for over a decade. Reported to CEOs for 13+ years. Built product organizations from zero to meaningful revenue, maintained high NPS, and shipped to millions.</p>
        <p>I've spent my career at the intersection of <strong>education and technology</strong> &mdash; building learning platforms, establishing enterprise partnerships, and leading teams through the messy, human work of making products people actually use.</p>
        <p>Now I'm building in public: writing a book, shipping AI-powered products, and documenting the process. Not to start a company &mdash; to show how product thinking applies when the tools are smarter than ever and the stakes keep getting higher.</p>
        <div class="about-links">
          <a class="about-link" href="#">LinkedIn &rarr;</a>
          <a class="about-link" href="#">Substack &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
